The paper deals with Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and their performance on ImageNet, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the correlations in the layer weight matrices of DNNs, which could fall under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a new capacity control metric for DNNs, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI).
